  "description": "In <i>Empire Builder</i> the player is a property developer in greater London and the goal is to make as much money as possible. The player starts with £500,000. First the player must decide for a company name and then select in which county to begin (there are 20 to choose among). From the game's main menu, the player can choose from the following options:\n<ul><li>Accounts/Banking: This screen shows the player's financial status.</li>\n<li>Build: Advances time 24 days.</li>\n<li>Property design: On this screen the player chooses how many properties of each type that is to be built.</li>\n<li>Building society: On this screen the player can invest money in property or savings.</li>\n<li>Job center: On this screen the player can hire workers.</li>\n<li>Legal eagle: Here you turn to engage a solicitor.</li>\n<li>Materials: Here you keep track of your materials and buy new one too.</li>\n<li>Office: This screen shows the player a menu where different reports can be accessed, company status for example.</li>\n<li>Site plan:  This screen shows the number of owned plots, built plots, sold plots and so on.</li>\n<li>Shares: The stock market, well sort of since the only stock that can be bought or sold is the one belonging to the player's company.</li>\n<li>Score: This screen shows the player the score.</li></ul>",
